\pard\f0\fs28    {\i T. virgata} var. {\i quadriaristata} (Biv.) Fiori & Paol., from Sicilia, is somewhat intermediate between {\b 1} and {\b 2}. It appears to be perennial and has a pappus of usually 4 long hairs, but the outer involucral bracts are about as long as the inner, curved and not appressed. It requires further investigation.
